<concept id="concept_1BCF5C425D7D4627AB1C66A085CF6E11" xml:lang="en-us">

                <title>Enable Login to APP and Service Controllers</title>
                <conbody>
                        <section>
                                <p>In order to be able to login to the Asynchronous Provisioning Platform (APP) and its service controllers, some settings have to be made in the administration portal: </p>
                        <ol>
                                <li>Choose <b>Manage organization</b> in the <b><b>Operation</b></b> menu. </li>
                                <li>Enter <codeph>PLATFORM_OPERATOR</codeph> in the <b>Organization ID</b> field. </li>
                                <li>Enable the following organization roles: <b>Supplier</b> and <b>Technology provider </b></li>
                                <li>Fill in the mandatory fields (red asterisks) </li>
                                <li>Click <b>Save</b>
                                </li>
                                <li>Go to the <b>Account</b> menu and choose <b>Manage users</b>
                                </li>
                                <li>Click on <codeph>administrator</codeph>
                                </li>
                                <li>Enter your Email address </li>
                                <li>Enable all user roles. </li>
                                <li>Click <b><b>Save</b></b>
                                </li>
                                <li>Logout of the administration portal and login again to enable the changes. </li>
                        </ol>
                        <p>Now you are able to login to APP: </p>
                        <p><codeph>http://&lt;hostname.fqdn>:8880/oscm-app/ </codeph></p>
                        <p>User name: <codeph>administrator</codeph>
                        </p>
                        <p>Password: <codeph>admin123 </codeph></p>
                        <p>You can also login to the instance status interface of the service controllers: </p>
                        <p><codeph>http://&lt;hostname.fqdn>:8880/oscm-app-&lt;controller-name>/ </codeph></p>
                        <p>User name: <codeph>administrator</codeph>
                        </p>
                        <p>Password: <codeph>admin123 </codeph></p>
                        <p><codeph>&lt;controller-name></codeph> can be <codeph>openstack</codeph>, <codeph>aws</codeph>, or <codeph>vmware</codeph>. </p>
                        </section>
                </conbody>
        </concept>
